### 5. Eager Test — `OrderProcessor_FullWorkflow_Succeeds` (line 54)

Calls **7 distinct production methods** in a single test. When this test fails, the stack trace points to one of seven possible causes — good luck diagnosing it.

```csharp
// ❌ Current — 7 production method calls
processor.ValidateOrder(order);
processor.CalculateTotal(order);
processor.ApplyDiscount(order, "SAVE10");
processor.ReserveInventory(order);
processor.ProcessPayment(order, new CreditCard("4111111111111111"));
processor.SendConfirmation(order);
processor.UpdateOrderHistory(order);
```

**Fix:** If this is a unit test, split into focused tests per method. If it's intentionally an integration/workflow test, rename and annotate it to make that clear:

```csharp
// ✅ Fixed — if it's meant to be an integration test
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("Integration")]
public void FullOrderWorkflow_EndToEnd_CompletesSuccessfully()
{
    // ... same body, but now the intent is explicit
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** Slow failure diagnosis; any production method regression breaks this one test with a non-obvious root cause.

